BELOW YOU WILL FIND AN EXTRACT FROM THE IMO`S RULE BOOK WHICH SETS OUT ALL THE
RULES YOU WILL NEED.ONLY THE APPENDICES FOR THE REFEREES AND STADIUM OWNERS
HAVE BEEN OMMITTED.
THE PLAYING FEILD IS 576 FEET LONG AND 320 GHOLDFOOT WIDE.AT EACH OF THE LONG
SIDES THERE IS A 26 GHOLDFOOT WIDE AND 35 GHOLDFOOT DEEP MOAT.DIRECTLY BEHIND
THE MOAT,THERE IS LOCATED EXACTLY IN THE CENTRE OF THE FIELD A 12 GHOLFFOOT
WIDE POTT(BUCKET)IN THE MOAT,THERE LURKS A CAR-NIVOROUS CREATURE,WHICH IS NOT
TO BE FED FOR 3 DAYS PRIOR TO THE BEGINNING OF THE GAME. THE PITCH IS DIVIDED
INTO 3 PARTS,THE THIRD NEAREST A TEAMS POTT IS THE DEFENCE AREA OF THE TEAM,
THE THIRD ADJACENT TO THE OPPONENTS POTT IS THE ATTACK AREA,TYHE THIRD IN THE
MIDDLE IS NO-MANS LAND.TEN TRIANGLES MARK THE START POSITIONS FOR INDIVIDUAL
PLAYERS.

GAME CREATURE:

THE GAME CREATURE IS A FLONK WEIGHING AT LEAST 5 GHOLDUNZ AND WHICH MUST BE
AT LEAST 12 YEARS OLD.SEVEN FLONKS ARE USED IN A GAME.THE FLONK IS THROWN INTO
THE CENTRE OF THE PITCH FROM EITHER THE RIGHT OR LEFT.IF A FLONK LANDS IN A
POTT,THEN ANOTHER FLONK IS THROWN ONTO THE PLAYING FIELD. IF A FLONK LANDS
OUTSIDE THE BOUNDARY OF THE PLAYING FIELD,HE IS THROWN BACK INTO PLAY FROM THE
POINT AT WHICH HE LANDS OUTSIDE THE BOUNDARY.THE REFEREE CONSTANTLY SUPERVISES
THE CONDITION OF THE FLONK IN PLAY.IF THE FLONK IS NO LONGER FIT TO PLAY,A NEW
FLONK IS THROWN ONTO THE PITCH AT THE SAME LEVEL WHICH THE LAST FLONK WAS
WITHDRAWN FROM THE GAME. THIS SUBSTITUTE FLONK DOES NOT COUNT AS AN ADDITONAL
FLONK - HE KEEPS THE SAME NUMBER AS THE FLONK WHICH WAS WITHDRAWN FROM THE
GAME,SO THAT 7 FLONKS MUST STILL LAND IN THE POTT.

AIM OF THE GAME:

THE AIM OF THE GAME IS TO SCORE AS MANY POINTS AS POSSIBLE,A TEAM IS AWARDED 1
POINT WHEN A PLAYER THROWS A FLONK INTO THE OPPOSING TEAMS POTT.THIS IS CALLED
A FLONKPOTT OR FLOPPT FOR SHORT.IF INSTEAD OF THROWING,A PLAYER SUCCEEDS IN
PLACING A FLONK DIRECTLY IN THE POTT BY JUMPING INTO THE MOAT THEN THIS COUNTS
AS A DOUBLE FLOPPT AND SCORES 2 POINTS.

END OF THE GAME: THE GAME IS OVER WHEN..

A) WHEN ALL 7 FLONKS HAVE LANDED IN THE POTT,IN THIS CASE THE TEAM WITH THE
HIGHEST NUMBER OF POINTS IS THE WINNER. IF THE POINTS SCORE IS EQUAL,THEN
ANOTHER FLONK IS THROWN IN. THE TEAM WHO POTTS HIM IS THE WINNER.

B) WHEN A TEAM IS UNABLE TO FIELD THE REQUIRED NUMBER OF PLAYERS ON PITCH,IN
THIS CASE,THE OTHER TEAM IS THE WINNER EVEN IF IT HAS LESS POINTS.

C) WHEN WAR BREAKS OUT. IN THIS CASE,THE GAME IS CALLED TO A HALT AND
POSTPONED.

FEILD PLAYERS:

EACH TEAM HAS 5 PLAYERS ON THE PITCH.THE 5 PLAYERS DISTRUBUTE THEMSELVES AMONG
THREE GROUPS. 2 DEFENSIVE PLAYERS (BLOCKERS) - 2 ATTACKERS(RUNNERS) - 1 CENTRE
PLAYER (HERO)...EACH OF THE 3 TEAMS MUST BE MADE UP OF PLAYERS OF THE SAME
RACE,PLAYERS OF 2 DIFFERENT RACES MAY NOT BE USED IN THE SAME GROUP. WHEN THE
FLONK IS THROWN INTO PLAY,ALL PLAYERS MUST BE LOCATED AT THEIR STARTING
POSITIONS.

FOULS:

FOULS ARE ONLY PENALISED WHEN THEY OCCUR WITHIN NO-MANS LAND. IN THE
ATTACKING/DEFENCE AREAS,BASICALLY EVERY ACTION IS ALLOWED ON THE PART OF THE
PLAYERS. IF A PLAYER TOUCHES ANOTHER PLAYER,WHO IS NOT IN FLONK POSITION,THEN
THIS COUNTS AS A FOUL.WHETHER CONTACT WAS HARMLESS,ACIDENTAL OR INTENTIONAL IS
LEFT TO THE JUDGEMENT OF THE REFEREE. THE PLAYERS IN FLONK [POSSESION MAY
CHARGE AND BE FOULED AT WILL.IN THE CASE OF A FOUL,A FREE THROW IS CARRIED
OUT.WHEN IT IS NOT JUST A CASE OF CONTACT.BUT A FIGHT LASTING MORE THAN HALF A
SECOND,THEN THE PLAYER WHO BEGAN THE FIGHT IS FROZEN FOR ABOUT 20 SECONDS.THIS
ALSO APPLIES WHEN THE INSTIGATOR OF THE FIGHT WAS IN FLONK POSSESSION.
IF THE REFEREE IS NOT ABLE TO DECIDE CLEARLY WHO BEGAN THE FIGHT,THEN THE GAME
IS INTERUPTED.BOTH PLAYERS CAN CONTINUE TO FIGHT AT WILL.
THE GAME IS NOT INTERUPTED WHEN THE FIGHT TAKES PLACE IN ONR OF THE DEFENSIVE
AREAS.(NOTE:IN OTHER WORDS YOU CAN DO ANYTHING AS LONG AS THE REF DOESN'T SEE
IT.) FOULS AGAINST THE REF IRRESPECTIVE OF WHEN AND WHERE ARE PENALISED WITH
THE PLAYERS IMMEDIATE ELIMINATION.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CHANGE OF PLAYERS:

THE TEAM COACH CAN ASK FOR TIME OUT WHEN THE FLONK IS IN NO-MANS LAND AND HIS
TEAM IS IN FLONK POSSESSION.IF THE FLONK IS IN AN ATTACK AREA,THEN NO TIME OUT
IS POSSIBLE.DURING THIS TIME,THE COACH IS ALLOWED TO SUBSTITUTE PLAYERS AS HE
WISHES. THERE IS NO LIMIT WHATSOEVER TO THE NUMBER OF PLAYER SUBSTITUTIONS.
AFTER THE SUBSTITUTION THE GAME MUST BE CONTINUED IMMEDIATELY. A PLAYER WHO IS
NO LONGER ABLE TO TAKE ACTIVE PART IN THE GAME MUST BE SUBBED IMMEDIATELY SO
AS NOT TO HINDER THE OTHER PLAYERS.IF THE TEAM IS UNABLE TO SUBSTITUTE A
PLAYER IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE RULES THEN THIS TEAM HAS LOST THE GAME.A PLAYER
IS CONSIDERED NO LONGER FIT TO PARTICIPATE WHEN THE REF NOTICES HIS LIFE
FUNCTIONS HAVE CEASED.THIS IS AT THE LATEST THE CASE WHEN THE PLAYER HAS LAIN
MOTIONLESS THIRTY SECONDS ON THE GROUND.SUCH A PLAYER IS BANNED FROM ALL
FURTHER GAMES.
