REFEREES:

THE REF INDICATES RULE INFRINGEMENTS BY GESTURE.THE GESTURES ARE AS FOLLOWS..

A) RIGHT HAND HELD ABOVE LEFT HAND IN SHAPE OF A `T`...
   - WHEN A PLAYER ASKS FOR TIME OUT,THIS GESTURE STARTS THE TIME OUT -

B) BOTH ARMS CROSSED, INDEX FINGER POINTING...
   - FREE KICK:THE EXECUTION OF A FREE KICK FOLLOWING A FOUL IS INDICATED THIS
   WAY -

C) LEFT HAND POINTING AT MID WAIST....
   - TEAM 1:INDICATES IN THE TEAM(IN THIS CASE FROM BOTTOM TO TOP)TO WHICH THE
    FOLLOWING GESTURES REFER -

D) RIGHT HAND ,INDEX FINGER POINTING TO THE RIGHT...
   - AS C,BUT FOR THE TEAMS PLAYING FROM TOP TO BOTTOM-       

E) 2 CLENCHED FISTS MEETING AT THE MID-RIFF...
   - INDICATES FIGHT IN NO-MANS LAND -

F) ARMS BENT AT THE ELBOWS.INDEX FINGERS POINTING DOWN.
   - PENALTY: PLAYER IS FROZEN FOR SOME TIME -

G) IS`NT SHOWN ON THE PAGE!!!!

H) REF LOOKING TO HIS RIGHT,WITH LEFT INDEX FINGER POINTING,AND HOLDING
   SOMETHING IN HIS RIGHT...
   - GESTURE TI INDICATE WHEN A PLAYER MUST BE TAKEN OUT OF THE GAME -

I) RIGHT HAND CLENCHED AT MID-RIFF WITH LEFT HAND PALM OPEN MID-RIF...
   - TACKLING OF A PLAYER IN NO-MANS LAND,WHO IS NOT IN POSSESSION OF THE
   BALL -

J) TONGUE OUT..LEFT HAND,INDEX FINGER POINTING TO THE RIGHT...
   - PENALTY: PLAYER IS REMOVED FROM THE GAME AND THE TEAM -

K) BOTH HANDS UP..INDEX FINGERS POINTING UP...
   - FLOPPT: AFTER THIS GESTURE THE NEW SCORE IS DISPLAYED -

L) REF HOLDING UP A ROUND BOARD(WITH A 2 ON IT)...
   - FLONK NUMBER INDICATES WHICH FLONK IS PRESENTLY THROWN IN -
